1-change over time- line plot
2-if you want to demonstrate how value rise and fall over time - area plot
3-if you want to compare -bar or colunm chart
4-view diffrent data sets at one glance or view to diffrent data set at one glance -grouped
5-make use of negatice to show subtraction from the total -negative
6-showing percentages or parts of a whole- pie chart
7-use your data to add 100$ -stacked bars
8-display progress - gauge chart
9-show distribution from least to most common -histogram
10-a large number of values against the second variable- scatter
11- bubble chart allows you to add a third dimension of dot size
